remotepimanager

Class TechCall

  • java.lang.Object
    • remotepimanager.TechCall

  • public class TechCall
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to handle two-way audio calls between a client and a device. Note: this is an adjusted version of the TechCall class that has the audio recording and sending features disabled due to issues running it on a Raspberry Pi device.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  TechCall.PlaybackThread
      Thread class that waits to receive bytes from socket in UDP format and plays them back using default system speakers
      class  TechCall.RecordingThread
      Thread class that records audio from default system microphone to a byte array and sends to the stored IP address using UDP packets

      Constructor method used to create new instance of TechCall that will wait to receive a UDP packet before returning a call

        public void startCall()
